1. A load balancer is a device that actas as a reverse proxy used to distribute network or application traffic across mutiple servers in a server farm. It is used to increase capacity and reliability of applications.

2. The load balancer software i am familiar with is Haproxy.

3. Healthcheck in load balancing is when a the load balancer checks the status of all it's registered servers to make sure they are running before routing traffic to it.

4. The first server to recieve traffic depends on the algorithm that is set in the load balancer

5. A forward proxy is an internet-facing proxy server used to control incoming traffic from the internet.

6. A LB is needed to help distribute traffic to multiple servers so as to increase the availability of the appand reponsiveness.

7.I have written a script of about 96 lines.
